<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900402-0128</DOCNO><DOCID>900402-0128.</DOCID><HL>   Hoechst Unit Merger</HL><DATE>04/02/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   G.HFA J.MKA</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   FRANKFURT, West Germany -- The West German chemical groupHoechst AG said it agreed to merge its latex paints businesswith that of Mitsubishi Kasei Corp. of Japan. Financial termsweren't disclosed.   Hoechst said the companies' respective paint operationswill be placed into an existing 50-50 joint venture company,Kasei Hoechst Co. Ltd., which for the past 23 years hasproduced and marketed reactive dyes.</LP><TEXT>   The agreement for the new business cooperation still needsthe approval of &quot;relevant authorities,&quot; Hoechst said, addingthat the merger is planned to take effect July 1.</TEXT></DOC>